---
const pills = ['Python', 'SQL', 'TensorFlow', 'GCP / BigQuery', 'Streamlit', 'DataRobot', 'Apache Spark', 'Docker', 'Tableau', 'Java'];
const facts = [
  {
    icon: '🌌',
    title: 'Dual B.S. in Astrophysics & CS',
    body: 'Rutgers University. Society of Physics member, minor in Mathematics. The kind of person who thinks statistical mechanics was just ML before it was cool.',
  },
  {
    icon: '📡',
    title: 'Hosted the Verizon Analytics Summit',
    body: 'Presented at the 2023 summit alongside executives from Verizon, Bayer, BNY Mellon, NY Life, and ThoughtSpot. No pressure.',
  },
  {
    icon: '🧬',
    title: 'Trained ML on mice',
    body: 'At the Human Genetics Institute of NJ, built DeepLabCut models for kinematic pose estimation on wet-lab video. Yes, really.',
  },
  {
    icon: '🎓',
    title: 'Georgia Tech MS in Computational Analytics',
    body: 'My honest stance on the degree: check back in 3 years to see if I actually get that 4.0.',
  },
];
---

<section id="about" class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-head reveal">
      <span class="section-label">About</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">The person<br>behind the models</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="about-grid">
    <div class="about-left reveal">
      <p class="body">
        I'm Geet. Recovering astrophysicist, Data Scientist at Verizon, lifelong sucker
        for a good anomaly. I started out studying black holes at Rutgers and somehow ended up
        hunting them in billion-dollar datasets instead.
        <strong>Turns out the universe is full of patterns whether you're looking at galaxies or customer churn.</strong>
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        I'm currently a few semesters into my Georgia Tech Master's in Computational Analytics,
        hanging in there by a <s>thread</s> token, but still going.
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        Outside of work: unhealthy amounts of anime, losing LP in League of Legends,
        and gym sessions to offset the desk time.
      </p>
      <div class="pills">
        {pills.map((p) => <span class="pill">{p}</span>)}
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-right">
      <div class="facts">
        {facts.map((f) => (
          <article class="fact reveal">
            <span class="fact-icon" aria-hidden="true">{f.icon}</span>
            <div class="fact-text">
              <h3 class="fact-title">{f.title}</h3>
              <p class="fact-body">{f.body}</p>
            </div>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  #about { border-top: 1px solid var(--border-soft); }
  .about-head { margin-bottom: clamp(36px, 5vw, 56px); }
  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: clamp(40px, 6vw, 84px);
    align-items: start;
  }
  .body {
    font-size: clamp(16.5px, 1.3vw, 19px);
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 22px;
  }
  .body strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 500; }
  .body s { color: var(--muted); }

  .pills { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 30px; }
  .pill {
    font-size: 14px;
    padding: 7px 15px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-pill);
    background: var(--surface);
    color: var(--text-dim);
    transition: color 0.25s, background 0.25s;
  }
  .pill:hover { color: var(--text); background: var(--surface-hover); }

  /* Facts as an editorial list, not a stack of boxes */
  .facts { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
  .fact {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 24px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-soft);
  }
  .fact:first-child { border-top: none; padding-top: 0; }
  /* Fixed-width icon column so titles and bodies share one left edge
     regardless of how wide each emoji renders. */
  .fact-icon {
    flex: none;
    width: 32px;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 21px;
    line-height: 25px; /* matches the title's line box for baseline alignment */
  }
  .fact-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 25px;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .fact-body { font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-dim); font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.65; }

  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .about-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
